Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
analyze_paths_...cal_false_path(25.10)  analyze_paths_...cal_false_path(25.10)

Name
       analyze_paths_by_critical_false_path   -   Identifies  violating  false
       paths, which are paths that appear as violations but  cannot  be  exer-
       cised  due to the structure of the netlist, and creates a category that
       contains them

Syntax
       analyze_paths_by_critical_false_path

       [-help]

       [-critical_false_paths {false_path_only | exclude_false_path}]

       [-master <string>]

       Identifies violating false paths, which are paths that appear as viola-
       tions but cannot be exercised due to the structure of the netlist,  and
       creates  a category that contains them. With this command the user can,
       in advance, categorize the critical false  paths  together  to  analyze
       them.

       The command can be applied wherever the user loads the machine readable
       timing report.

       For  more  information  on creating path categories, see "Creating Path
       Categories" in the Debugging Timing Results chapter of User Guide.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each analyze_paths_by_critical_false_path para-
              meter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man analyze_paths_by_critical_false_path

       -critical_false_paths
              Specifies which paths to analyze. You can select one of the fol-
              lowing options:

              * false_path_only

                Includes only false paths when creating the category.

              * exclude_false_path

                Excludes false paths when creating the category.

              Default: false_path_only

       -master <string>
              Specifies  that  the  analysis  should be performed only for the
              specified master category.

Examples:
              * The following command creates path  categories  based  on  the
                critical false paths:

                analyze_paths_by_critical_false_path      -critical_false_path
                false_path_only

              * The    following    category    is    created:     default_re-
                port_false_path_only

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

